---
import SiteLayout from "../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
import PageHero from "../../components/PageHero.astro";
import ServiceCta from "../../components/ServiceCta.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import bannerImage from "../../assets/photos/rov-inspection-lights.jpg";
import controllerImage from "../../assets/photos/rov-controller-hands.jpg";
import chainImage from "../../assets/photos/rov-chain-shackle.jpg";
import hudImage from "../../assets/photos/inspection-hud.jpg";
import launchImage from "../../assets/photos/rov-launch-gunwale.jpg";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Inspection | MarineStream™"
  description="High-definition ROV and diver surveys with live multi-stakeholder access and fouling ratings captured at the point of survey."
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Services"
    title="Inspection"
    lead="Hull, propeller, and niche-area surveys with fouling ratings captured at the point of survey."
    parent={{ href: "/services", label: "Services" }}
    image={bannerImage}
    imageAlt="Inspection ROV with lights on approaching a fouled mooring chain"
  />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <span class="eyebrow">Overview</span>
      <h2>See the condition before it becomes a problem</h2>
      <hr class="accent-rule" />
      <p>
        An inspection is only as useful as the decisions it enables. MarineStream surveys rate
        fouling at the point of survey, stream footage to every stakeholder who needs it, and land
        the evidence in one auditable record, so a clean, a treatment, or a clearance can be
        approved without a second visit.
      </p>
      <ul class="checklist checklist--cols">
        <li>4K imaging and HD recording</li>
        <li>Positioning and sonar for repeatable coverage</li>
        <li>Fouling ratings captured at the point of survey</li>
        <li>Live multi-stakeholder access to footage</li>
        <li>Hull, propeller, sea chest, and niche-area coverage</li>
        <li>Direct MarineStream™ platform integration</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--soft">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid-2">
        <div class="reveal">
          <span class="eyebrow">What we survey</span>
          <h2>Vessels, moorings, and infrastructure</h2>
          <hr class="accent-rule" />
          <p>
            The same workflow covers ship hulls and the assets around them: mooring chains,
            anchors, wharf structures, and submerged infrastructure. ROV surveys reach what divers
            should not, and diver surveys carry the same rating and recording discipline where
            hands-on access is needed.
          </p>
          <p>
            Every frame is tagged to the asset and zone it belongs to, which is what makes the
            record auditable rather than a folder of video files.
          </p>
        </div>
        <figure class="figure reveal">
          <Image
            src={chainImage}
            alt="Fouled mooring chains converging at a shackle with an inspection ROV on task"
            widths={[480, 900]}
            sizes="(min-width: 800px) 32rem, 100vw"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption>Mooring chain survey. The fouling is the finding, the ROV is the tool.</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">How a survey runs</span>
      <h2>Four steps, one record</h2>
      <hr class="accent-rule" />
      <ol class="steps">
        <li>
          <strong>Mobilise</strong>
          <p>ROV or dive team deploys from wharf or vessel with the survey plan loaded.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Survey</strong>
          <p>Systematic coverage of hull, niches, or infrastructure with positioning logged.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Rate</strong>
          <p>Fouling rated in the field, on the spot, against the agreed scale.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Report</strong>
          <p>Evidence, ratings, and sign-offs land in the platform. Reports generate automatically.</p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--soft">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid-2">
        <figure class="figure reveal" style="margin: 0;">
          <Image
            src={hudImage}
            alt="Inspection system interface showing a fouled hull section with depth and zone telemetry"
            widths={[480, 900]}
            sizes="(min-width: 800px) 32rem, 100vw"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption>
            Live inspection telemetry: depth, heading, and hull zone recorded with every frame.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
        <div class="reveal">
          <span class="eyebrow">The evidence layer</span>
          <h2>Stakeholders watch the same survey</h2>
          <hr class="accent-rule" />
          <p>
            Owners, regulators, and class surveyors do not wait for an edited report. Live access
            means questions are answered during the survey, and the record everyone saw is the
            record that gets signed.
          </p>
          <p>
            Partners use these workflows to deliver consistent, auditable surveys without
            reinventing reporting for every client and jurisdiction.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <span class="eyebrow">In the field</span>
      <h2>Equipment matched to the job</h2>
      <hr class="accent-rule" />
      <div class="photo-pair">
        <Image
          src={launchImage}
          alt="Technician launching an ROV over a vessel gunwale"
          widths={[480, 800]}
          sizes="(min-width: 560px) 21rem, 100vw"
          loading="lazy"
        />
        <Image
          src={controllerImage}
          alt="Operator's hands on an ROV controller showing a live underwater feed"
          widths={[480, 800]}
          sizes="(min-width: 560px) 21rem, 100vw"
          loading="lazy"
        />
      </div>
      <p>
        Inspection-class ROVs handle the routine coverage. Divers take the niches that need hands
        and judgement. Both feed the same record. If you want the equipment itself, see
        <a href="/services/hardware">hardware</a>, and if you want your own teams surveying to this
        standard, see <a href="/services/training">training</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <ServiceCta
    title="Book a survey, or build the capability"
    lead="Tell us the vessel or asset and the standard you need to meet. We will scope the survey, or set your team up to run it."
    primaryHref="/contact"
    primaryLabel="Enquire about inspection"
    secondaryHref="/services/cleaning"
    secondaryLabel="Cleaning with capture"
  />
</SiteLayout>
